{"talk":{"id":10361,"name":"Petter Johansson: Do you really know why you do what you do?","description":"Experimental psychologist Petter Johansson researches choice blindness -- a phenomenon where we convince ourselves that we're getting what we want, even when we're not. In an eye-opening talk, he shares experiments (designed in collaboration with magicians!) that aim to answer the question: Why do we do what we do? The findings have big implications for the nature of self-knowledge and how we react in the face of manipulation. You may not know yourself as well as you think you do.","slug":"petter_johansson_do_you_really_know_why_you_do_what_you_do","recorded_at":"2016-11-11 00:00:00","published_at":"2018-03-06 16:00:08","updated_at":"2021-04-09 19:39:38","viewed_count":1233580,"emailed_count":0,"event":{"id":487,"name":"TEDxUppsalaUniversity"},"images":[{"image":{"size":"113x85","url":"https:\/\/pe.tedcdn.com\/images\/ted\/41df717b74a6b78e80f47d6baa300c5adabdff46_113x85.jpg"}},{"image":{"size":"240x180","url":"https:\/\/pe.tedcdn.com\/images\/ted\/41df717b74a6b78e80f47d6baa300c5adabdff46_240x180.jpg"}},{"image":{"size":"615x461","url":"https:\/\/pe.tedcdn.com\/images\/ted\/41df717b74a6b78e80f47d6baa300c5adabdff46_615x461.jpg"}},{"image":{"size":"2400x1800","url":"https:\/\/pe.tedcdn.com\/images\/ted\/41df717b74a6b78e80f47d6baa300c5adabdff46_2400x1800.jpg"}}],"image_16x9":"https:\/\/pe.tedcdn.com\/images\/ted\/2fc9fe406ea4f167c57c57da3475bb65e47ba3e3_2880x1620.jpg","media":{"internal":{"64k":{"uri":"https:\/\/download.ted.com\/talks\/PetterJohansson_2016X-64k.mp4?apikey=c692baa7dafbf74e4fbde1ac88b44cafc96cfe7a","filesize_bytes":7985282,"mime_type":"video\/mp4"},"180k":{"uri":"https:\/\/download.ted.com\/talks\/PetterJohansson_2016X-180k.mp4?apikey=c692baa7dafbf74e4fbde1ac88b44cafc96cfe7a","filesize_bytes":22139091,"mime_type":"video\/mp4"},"320k":{"uri":"https:\/\/download.ted.com\/talks\/PetterJohansson_2016X-320k.mp4?apikey=c692baa7dafbf74e4fbde1ac88b44cafc96cfe